# Rust build artifacts
/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Cargo
Cargo.lock.bak

# IDE / editors
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local env / secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Profiling / coverage
*.profraw
*.profdata
/coverage/
flamegraph.svg
perf.data*

# Python artifacts (for compatibility test harnesses, later)
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# CPython test scratch files: `test.support.TESTFN` is `@test_<pid>_tmp`, which
# tests drop in the CWD and don't always clean up when run via the conformance
# harness. Mirrors CPython's own .gitignore so these never get staged.
@test_*

# Generated docs
/book/
/site/

# Local scratch / throwaway diagnostics
.scratch/

# Vendored CPython checkout for the regrtest harness (opt-in, machine-local).
# The conformance runner auto-discovers vendor/cpython/Lib/test/ when present;
# we never commit it (size + licensing) — see docs/CONFORMANCE.md.
#
# Ignore everything under vendor/ EXCEPT the lightly-patched lzma-sys crate,
# which is a committed build input wired via Cargo.toml [patch.crates-io].
/vendor/*
!/vendor/lzma-sys/
